Name: BILLI
Comment:
We strongly condemns violence and this total incident of redfort. But this only half story. Just take a second and think, farmers were protesting peacefully from about 5 months(3 in punjab and 2 in delhi) do what happened all of sudden that they become so violent? 1st thing 1st, government and police already knew that something is going to happen (check godi media's news of last 3 days). They were worried about some anti-social elements from Pakistan. Is our Indian police force so weak?Police didn't stop protesters when only 20 tractors reached redfort, they were just sitting under the sun(check video from ndtv handle as prove) question is why they waited? Only when 100s of tractors gathered, they used tear gas and lathi march as a result people became violent. These were just 2% of total protesting farmers and they went under leadership of Deep sidhu(bjp supporter). Other 98% farmers were tractor marching peacefully as decided by delhi police. But godi media covered only those 2% farmers. Another thing, Indian flag was not harmed at all. It was above all. Other 2 flags were hoisted but at lower level (which was inturn wrong and i criticise that). But think if government wanted, they could stop them at very initial stage but they didn't in order to defame and discredit the whole movement. Because its very easy for gov. to shut down violent movement. Moreover 155 farmers have lost their life protesting peacefully. Who is responsible for their loss even during peaceful protest? They are also humans but this godi media don't leave a single chance to show farmer protest as anti natinalist. Just think about those 98% others and not just these government motivated 2%.
History shows only peaceful protest stay for that long to be won. Best way to disrupt any protest is to invite violence.

Do your research and then conclude .
Peace!
